#error "Please select first the target STM32F4xx device used in your application (in stm32f4xx.h file)"
Solution: 
Define in your project settings (recommended)
1. Right-click project → Properties
2. Go to C/C++ Build → Settings → MCU GCC Compiler → Preprocessor (or C/C++ General → Paths and Symbols → Symbols)
3. Add Preprocessor Macro:
     STM32F446xx
This tells CMSIS you’re targeting STM32F446 (Nucleo-F446RE)
